00:27:02.170 --> 00:27:04.770
but it's something called
differential rotation.

00:27:04.770 --> 00:27:07.300 position:56%
So, think for a second about planets

00:27:07.300 --> 00:27:10.570
like Jupiter, Saturn,
the gas giants.

00:27:10.570 --> 00:27:12.760
Okay. These are not solid planets.

00:27:12.760 --> 00:27:16.600 position:56%
When they rotate, they rotate faster

00:27:16.600 --> 00:27:22.020
as they get towards the
equator they rotate faster.

00:27:22.020 --> 00:27:24.660
As you move towards the
poles they rotate slower.

00:27:24.660 --> 00:27:26.410
That's why you see
those bands for example.

00:27:26.410 --> 00:27:27.950
Because they're not solid.

00:27:27.950 --> 00:27:29.420
Well, the sun is not solid.

00:27:29.420 --> 00:27:31.930
The sun is a plasma as I mentioned.

00:27:31.930 --> 00:27:37.030
And so, that means that it doesn't
rotate at the same rate when you're

00:27:37.030 --> 00:27:39.480
at the equator versus the poles.

00:27:39.480 --> 00:27:41.630
So, it's a plasma.

00:27:41.630 --> 00:27:45.850
Plasma are attracted to
electricity and magnetism.

00:27:45.850 --> 00:27:49.150
So, what happens is it means
that when this plasma moves,

00:27:49.150 --> 00:27:52.690
it drags magnetic fields with it.

00:27:52.690 --> 00:27:54.710
Okay. So, they're connected.

00:27:54.710 --> 00:27:56.800
They're coupled to each other.

00:27:56.800 --> 00:28:00.710
Now the sun, in its
simplest state is also

00:28:00.710 --> 00:28:02.480
like the earth, like
a giant bar magnet.

00:28:02.480 --> 00:28:06.790
So, it has magnetic fields
that go from north to south,

00:28:06.790 --> 00:28:08.280
south to north through it.

00:28:08.280 --> 00:28:10.600
And so, they're kind of this way.

