00:50:39.340 --> 00:50:41.690
of the thing we have to think
about for space weather.

00:50:41.690 --> 00:50:45.670
So, remember that all of
this stuff is happening,

00:50:45.670 --> 00:50:47.660
because again it's electromagnetic.

00:50:47.660 --> 00:50:50.810
All of that material is
plasma, which response

00:50:50.810 --> 00:50:52.960
to electricity and magnetism.

00:50:52.960 --> 00:50:55.560
And it's carrying magnetic
fields with it.

00:50:55.560 --> 00:50:59.570
So, all of the phenomena
that we're talking

00:50:59.570 --> 00:51:02.410
about is electromagnetic in nature.

00:51:02.410 --> 00:51:04.530
And so, what does that mean?

00:51:04.530 --> 00:51:08.820
That means that it
impacts technology.

00:51:08.820 --> 00:51:10.550
So, a couple of things happen.

00:51:10.550 --> 00:51:13.650
So, I mentioned those particles.

00:51:13.650 --> 00:51:18.740
The flare and the CME create those
high-energy particles you saw

00:51:18.740 --> 00:51:20.040
on the camera.

00:51:20.040 --> 00:51:24.410
Those impact spacecraft,
they can damage electronics.

00:51:24.410 --> 00:51:26.460
There should be an astronaut
floating around up here

00:51:26.460 --> 00:51:28.650
who would also be in danger.

00:51:28.650 --> 00:51:35.240
The other thing is that when you
saw that model of the magnetosphere

00:51:35.240 --> 00:51:38.670
and this big blast hit it, and
it starts wiggling like this

00:51:38.670 --> 00:51:40.100
and everything starts moving.

00:51:40.100 --> 00:51:43.000
Magnetic fields when
they move quickly,

00:51:43.000 --> 00:51:44.700
they create electrical currents.

00:51:44.700 --> 00:51:49.790
That's the physics behind
generators and motors.

00:51:49.790 --> 00:51:55.060
You're moving a magnetic field very
quickly it generates electricity.

00:51:55.060 --> 00:51:59.020
Well, that happens in the
outer atmosphere of the earth.

00:51:59.020 --> 00:52:01.420
So, there are currents
that are generated up here.

00:52:01.420 --> 00:52:04.490
Now, those currents
also give us the Aurora.

00:52:04.490 --> 00:52:07.720
They help to create, and
accelerate the particles

00:52:07.720 --> 00:52:09.020
and give us the Aurora.

00:52:09.020 --> 00:52:13.260
But, it impacts communications.

00:52:13.260 --> 00:52:14.790
It's disrupts GPS.

00:52:14.790 --> 00:52:19.040
It doesn't necessarily stop GPS,
but it makes it less accurate.

00:52:19.040 --> 00:52:24.310
So, if your GPS is telling
you something is right here,

00:52:24.310 --> 00:52:27.110 position:56%
the accuracy could be 10 times worse

00:52:27.110 --> 00:52:30.210
and it could actually be
you know a couple of meters,

00:52:30.210 --> 00:52:33.020 position:56%
or even a couple of kilometers away.

00:52:33.020 --> 00:52:40.110
That may not be as big a deal for
us, but these days we have farming

00:52:40.110 --> 00:52:44.160
that uses automated tractors
that are running on GPS.

00:52:44.160 --> 00:52:46.410
We even have, this is crazy.

00:52:46.410 --> 00:52:48.830
I talked to a friend of
mine who drives trucks.

00:52:48.830 --> 00:52:53.060
We even have people who drive
trucks around dangerous mountains

00:52:53.060 --> 00:52:56.740
in bad weather using GPS.

00:52:56.740 --> 00:53:01.810
But we drill in the ocean
for oil, or things like that.

00:53:01.810 --> 00:53:06.660
Doing even complicated construction
we use GPS for where things are.

00:53:06.660 --> 00:53:09.150
So, that's a huge issue.

00:53:09.150 --> 00:53:12.300
It impacts communications
on airplanes.

00:53:12.300 --> 00:53:18.270 position:56%
One of the issues is airplanes can't
be out of contact for less than,

00:53:18.270 --> 00:53:20.020
somewhere on the scale of minutes,

00:53:20.020 --> 00:53:26.110
when it's talking to
various airports.

00:53:26.110 --> 00:53:29.620
These storms, these occurrence,

00:53:29.620 --> 00:53:31.780
they're generated closer
to the poles.

00:53:31.780 --> 00:53:35.100
So, the magnetic fields
go from pole to pole.

00:53:35.100 --> 00:53:37.560
So, they go like this in this loop.

00:53:37.560 --> 00:53:41.070
When they come into the
North Pole or the South Pole,

00:53:41.070 --> 00:53:42.990
that's where the magnetic
field is weakest.

00:53:42.990 --> 00:53:45.040
And that's where the
storms are the strongest.

00:53:45.040 --> 00:53:49.210
That's why we see Aurora mostly
near the North and South Pole.

00:53:49.210 --> 00:53:53.630
As a storm becomes stronger, we
see these Aurora move farther

00:53:53.630 --> 00:53:55.720
and farther, closer to the equator.

00:53:55.720 --> 00:53:58.340
The storms are actually
moving down the equator.

00:53:58.340 --> 00:53:59.680
That's what's happening.

00:53:59.680 --> 00:54:02.360
But if you're in an airplane
and you're traveling from DC

00:54:02.360 --> 00:54:06.000
to Hong Kong you want to
travel over the poles.

00:54:06.000 --> 00:54:10.110
That's the shortest distance,
but you can travel over the poles

00:54:10.110 --> 00:54:13.840
if the communications are
out because of a solar storm.

00:54:13.840 --> 00:54:17.230
So, they have to travel
around instead,

00:54:17.230 --> 00:54:20.250
which means that they spend
a lot more fuel and a lot

00:54:20.250 --> 00:54:22.310
of money, and a lot more time.

00:54:22.310 --> 00:54:24.820
So, that's an issue for them.

00:54:24.820 --> 00:54:30.410
Also, if you're traveling as a
pilot or an airline attendant

00:54:30.410 --> 00:54:34.590
for long periods of time
over, you know many years,

00:54:34.590 --> 00:54:36.270
you are exposed to more radiation.

00:54:36.270 --> 00:54:38.220
Because you're higher up.

00:54:38.220 --> 00:54:40.270
So, that's an issue too.

00:54:40.270 --> 00:54:42.180
They don't want people
to be traveling

00:54:42.180 --> 00:54:44.870
through the poles during a storm.

00:54:44.870 --> 00:54:48.060
One of those particle storms.

00:54:48.060 --> 00:54:52.550
And then one of the other issues
is these currents are generated

00:54:52.550 --> 00:54:54.160
up in the atmosphere.

00:54:54.160 --> 00:54:57.420
They're also generated
down on the ground.

00:54:57.420 --> 00:55:02.390
Because when currents run
near a transmission line,

00:55:02.390 --> 00:55:04.360
okay near a conductor.

00:55:04.360 --> 00:55:08.780
In this case, let's say
between two electrical poles

00:55:08.780 --> 00:55:10.400
that are a kilometer apart.

00:55:10.400 --> 00:55:12.070
That's a long transmission line.

00:55:12.070 --> 00:55:14.040
That actually picks
up those currents

00:55:14.040 --> 00:55:16.030
and currents are generated in that.

00:55:16.030 --> 00:55:18.790 position:56%
If those currents are strong enough,

00:55:18.790 --> 00:55:20.640
and this is actually
much more analogous

00:55:20.640 --> 00:55:23.210
to the storm hitting your house.

00:55:23.210 --> 00:55:26.070
Those currents can
overload transformers,

00:55:26.070 --> 00:55:27.770
and they can take out power grids.

00:55:27.770 --> 00:55:29.350
And we've seen this happen,

00:55:29.350 --> 00:55:35.350
1989 we had the entire
Quebec power grid went out.

00:55:35.350 --> 00:55:39.740
And there have been other
storms that have hit.

00:55:39.740 --> 00:55:49.880
Generally, mostly communities in
places like a Sweden or Norway

00:55:49.880 --> 00:55:51.580
or something like that because
they're close to the poles.

00:55:51.580 --> 00:55:52.990
But, if they're strong enough,

00:55:52.990 --> 00:55:55.930
they can reach farther south,
and they can impact us.

00:55:55.930 --> 00:55:59.090
So, that's another area that
we have to be concerned on.

00:55:59.090 --> 00:56:03.730
Now, one thing to think about is
that the good thing is that all

00:56:03.730 --> 00:56:06.060
of these industries
are well aware of this.

00:56:06.060 --> 00:56:09.060
So, they pay close attention
to the weather report

00:56:09.060 --> 00:56:11.240
when it comes to space weather.

00:56:11.240 --> 00:56:13.700
And they take certain actions.

00:56:13.700 --> 00:56:15.610
As I said, they reroute planes,

00:56:15.610 --> 00:56:19.110
or they may change transformer
settings and things like that.

00:56:19.110 --> 00:56:22.370
So, it's something that they
do pay close attention to.

